## Mitigate Theft
Stop Expensive Insurance Claims
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/DriverVerification.de75d479510256b12514.png)
### Track your Shipments
Real-Time Notifications and Tracking
Receive immediate verification statuses and fraud detection alerts that stops theft before it can ever happen at all stages in the delivery.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/ApplicationAndMobile.e62f35439cec97468613.png)
### Stop Theft Before It Happens
Real-Time Verification
Full toolkit of Real-Time verification tools you can quickly use with all your logistics partners, with integration options available.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/DriverVerificationPage.5333ec094db37a05cd30.png)
### Enhance Security
Verifying Every Handoff
Verify driver identities, vehicles, and shipments against a source of truth government databases, as well as fraud and risk signal lookups.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/shipment-information.4aff08758e1c43f181c9.png)
### Fraudulent Document Detection
Real-Time Document Verification
Catch shipping document tampering in Real-Time, with all information extraction tooling to monitor for tampered documents.
## Stop Expensive Damage Claims
Track the Conditions of Your Cargo
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/CustomerPortalWide.1f5495ddec9a0d442b27.png)
### External Portal
Give your stakeholders full visibility
Give your freight forwarders, supply chain teams and cargo owners access to a portal where they can schedule deliveries, track cargo, and view reports and photos associated with each delivery.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/NotifyStakeholdersSquare.ab480a0c4d8a0398cbc6.png)
### Notify Stakeholders
Live Updates to All Stakeholders
Build notification and cargo photo workflows to notify stakeholders of the status of your cargo.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/MobileAppSquare.f352578743ef1d32519a.png)
### Live Photo Evidence
Mobile App for Easy Photo Capture
Easy to use mobile app for capturing photos of your cargo at every stage of the delivery process with geolocation tracking and device capture.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/ReportPage.2acd5993591bed25caf8.png)
### Cargo Documentation
Auto-generated Reports
Track the conditions of your cargo by taking a photo when it's loaded and delivered, with geolocation tracking and device capture. Then send auto-generated reports to all relevant stakeholders.
## Catch Double Brokering and Identity Theft
Automatically Vet Carriers and Catch Identity Theft.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/DriverVerification.de75d479510256b12514.png)
### Catch Fraudulent Carriers
Verify Carrier Authority & Insurance
Automatically verify DOT authority, insurance coverage, and safety ratings in real-time before every load assignment
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/ApplicationAndMobile.e62f35439cec97468613.png)
### Fraud Signal Detection
Detect Fraudulent Applications
Capture signals of fraudulent applications, including suspicious documents, devices, phone numbers, and more.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/DriverVerificationPage.5333ec094db37a05cd30.png)
### Verify the Business
Verify who is handling your cargo
Use information from trusted sources to verify who is behind the application.
![](http://www.indemni.com/static/media/VerifyCompliance.16a0c8c1904584f6e39f.png)
### Ensure Compliance
Verify Compliance & Safety
Verify compliance and safety metrics with all publicly available relevant regulations and standards.

generated_description:
Indemni is a promising start-up founded in 2024 and located in San Francisco. They are on a mission to tackle a significant issue in the logistics sector: cargo theft and fraud. Cargo theft is a growing problem that chips away at the profit margins of suppliers and shippers, making security a top priority for the entire supply chain industry. Indemni’s platform aims to create a safer supply chain by utilizing advanced technology and their extensive experience in fraud prevention from notable delivery marketplaces and logistics tech firms.

The company's approach integrates real-time identity verification and tracking to prevent theft before it occurs, which is a game changer. With just a small team of two employees and under the guidance of Y Combinator’s Group Partner, Pete Koomen, Indemni is part of the Y Combinator Batch W24—a stamp of approval that adds credibility.

What sets Indemni apart is its comprehensive suite of tools aimed at various participants in the supply chain—shippers, warehouses, and logistics providers. They offer a veritable treasure trove of features: from tracking shipments with real-time notifications to verifying identities and ensuring that all documents are secure.

Their services include:
- **Real-Time Tracking:** Users receive immediate alerts about the status of their cargo, allowing proactive responses to any discrepancies.
- **Identity Verification:** With verification tools for drivers and cargo, they enhance security at every step of the delivery. 
- **Fraud Detection:** Their platform detects potential theft signals and fraudulent applications before any harm can be done.
- **Stakeholder Transparency:** Indemni provides portals and mobile apps to keep all parties informed and connected, ensuring everyone has access to necessary information about the cargo.

Indemni’s website showcases their straightforward goal: "Protect Your Cargo. Prevent Theft. Maximize Profits." Their focus is on enhancing operational efficiency and profitability while creating a safe environment for goods in transit.

If you're interested in learning more or scheduling a demo, visiting [Indemni's website](http://www.indemni.com) is a great next step. As the logistics landscape evolves, solutions like Indemni's will be vital in addressing security issues and ensuring smoother operations within the supply chain.
